SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GREATER ALBUQUERQUE CHAMBER OF COMMERCE IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(6) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THE CHAMBER HAS ADOPTED ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, AS THEY RELATE TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS, AND HAVE EVALUATED TAX POSITIONS TAKEN FOR OPEN TAX YEARS. CURRENTLY, THE 2015, 2016 AND 2017 TAX YEARS ARE OPEN AND SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE AND NEW MEXICO TAXATION AND REVENUE DEPARTMENT. HOWEVER, THE CHAMBER IS NOT CURRENTLY UNDER AUDIT, NOR HAS THE CHAMBER BEEN CONTACTED BY ANY OF THESE JURISDICTIONS. ANY INTEREST AND PENALTIES RECOGNIZED ASSOCIATED WITH A TAX POSITION WOULD BE CLASSIFIED AS CURRENT IN THE CHAMBER'S CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. NO INTEREST OR PENALTIES WERE RECORDED IN 2018 OR 2017. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THAT THE ACTIVITIES OF THE CHAMBER ARE WITHIN THEIR TAX-EXEMPT PURPOSE, AND THAT THERE ARE NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS. THEREFORE, NO PROVISION FOR THE EFFECTS OF UNCERTAIN INCOME TAXES HAS BEEN RECORDED FOR THE YEARS ENDED JUNE 30, 2018 AND 2017.

TERRI L. COLE, PRESIDENT: EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE WHICH INCLUDES: THE CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD, THE CHAIR ELECT AND THE IMMEDIATE PAST CHAIR. THIS COMMITTEE, BECAUSE OF ITS COMPOSITION, PROVIDES CONTINUITY. ANNUAL GOALS ARE SET AT THE BEGINNING OF THE YEAR AND REVIEWED (ANNUALLY AFTER THE AUDIT). A BONUS IS GIVEN IF GOALS ARE MET AND IF REVENUE IS AVAILABLE. OTHER VARIABLES, SUCH AS DOING A MARKET COMPARISON OF SALARIES WITH OTHER CHAMBERS OF THE SAME SIZE, ARE ALSO FACTORED IN THE DETERMINATION OF THE SALARY FOR THE YEAR. PART II: CLARIFICATION ON OFFICER COMPENSATION REPORTING: IN ACCORDANCE WITH FORM 990 REPORTING REQUIREMENTS, THE COMPENSATION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S PRESIDENT REPORTED ON THIS SCHEDULE J, PART II IS ALSO REPORTED IN FULL ON THE IRS FORM 990 SCHEDULE J FOR CAREER GUIDANCE INSTITUTE. CAREER GUIDANCE INSTITUTE IS A RELATED TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATION IDENTIFIED ON SCHEDULE R.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GREATER ALBUQUERQUE CHAMBER OF COMMERCE'S (GACC) BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS COMPRISED PRIMARILY OF CEO'S OF VARIOUS BUSINESSES IN THE GREATER ALBUQUERQUE NEW MEXICO AREA. DUE TO THE LARGE SIZE OF THE GACC BOARD OF DIRECTORS, THERE ARE BOARD MEMBERS WHO MAY HAVE BUSINESS TRANSACTIONS WITH OTHER BOARD MEMBERS IN THE ORDINARY COURSE OF THEIR OWN BUSINESSES. THE GACC HAS A WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY THAT ALL BOARD MEMBERS RECEIVE. IF A SITUATION ARISES WHERE THERE MIGHT BE A CONFLICT RELATED TO A GACC TRANSACTION, THE AFFECTED BOARD MEMBER RECUSES THEMSELVES FROM BOTH THE DISCUSSION AND VOTE ON THAT MATTER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GREATER ALBUQUERQUE CHAMBER OF COMMERCE (GACC) BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS COMPRISED PRIMARILY OF CEO'S OF VARIOUS BUSINESSES IN THE GREATER ALBUQUERQUE NEW MEXICO AREA. DUE TO THE LARGE SIZE OF THE GACC BOARD OF DIRECTORS, THERE ARE BOARD MEMBERS WHO MAY HAVE BUSINESS TRANSACTIONS WITH OTHER BOARD MEMBERS IN THE ORDINARY COURSE OF THEIR OWN BUSINESSES, OR OCCASIONALLY WITH GACC ITSELF. TO ENSURE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST DO NOT ARISE, GACC HAS A WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY THAT APPLIES TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS AND OFFICERS. THE PROCESS THAT GACC USES TO REGULARLY AND CONSISTENTLY MONITOR AND ENFORCE COMPLIANCE WITH THIS POLICY ARE AS FOLLOWS: THE GACC WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS PROVIDED TO EACH BOARD MEMBER UPON ACCEPTING A POSITION ON THE GACC BOARD OF DIRECTORS AT THEIR INITIAL BOARD MEMBER ORIENTATION MEETING. AT THE ORIENTATION MEETING, THE POLICY IS REVIEWED IN DETAIL WITH EACH NEW BOARD MEMBER. AT THE GACC ANNUAL BOARD OF DIRECTORS MEETING EACH YEAR, THE BOARD REVIEWS THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND EACH BOARD MEMBER IS AGAIN PROVIDED WITH A COPY OF THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. FOR BOARD MEMBERS THAT DID NOT ATTEND THE ANNUAL BOARD MEETING, A COPY OF THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS PROVIDED TO THEM WITH A COPY OF THE ANNUAL BOARD OF DIRECTOR MEETING MINUTES.

A BONUS IS GIVEN IF GOALS ARE MET AND IF REVENUE IS AVAILABLE.
